<HEADLINE>
KIDD EARNS LEAGUE HONOR  
 OFFENSE BELONGS TO PLAYMAKER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB YOUNG  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - No wonder Suns playmaker &UR; Jason Kidd needed some rest
in the club's final regular-season games.
</P>
<P>
   Kidd was named the NBA's Player of the Month for April Monday
after accounting for more than 43 percent of the team's offensive
production last month, according to the league.
</P>
<P>
   The Suns were 10-6 in April with Kidd averaging 20.1 points,
10.4 assists, 6.7 rebounds and 2.38 steals while playing an average
of 42.6 minutes a game. Thus, he either scored or assisted on at
least 43 percent of the team's 94.2 points a game during the month.
</P>
<P>
   The Suns had not determined how many of the field goals Kidd
assisted on were three-point shots, so the percentage is actually
greater than 43 percent.
</P>
<P>
   Kidd also recorded two of the league-leading seven
triple-doubles he has this season during April.
</P>
<P>
   Kidd is the first Suns player to win the award since &UR; Kevin
Johnson was named Player of the Month in 1997, also for the month
of April. &QL; 
Playoff tickets
</P>
<P>
   Tickets for Game 3 of the team's first-round playoff series go
on sale today at 10 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   It is yet to be determined whether the Suns will play Portland,
Utah or San Antonio in a five-game first-round series. No matter
the opponent, the Suns will play the first two games on the road.
</P>
<P>
   Tickets can be purchased at America West Arena's ticket office
or by calling 379-SUNS or Dillard ticket outlets at 503-5555.
Tickets for Game 4, if necessary, will go on sale the day after
Game 3. There are plenty of seats available for Game 3. &QL; 
Playoff special
</P>
<P>
   Channel 45 will air a half-hour Suns playoff special Thursday
night at 9:30 p.m. Forward &UR; Clifford Robinson, a candidate for the
All-Defensive Team and one of the best three-point shooters this
season, will be the centerpiece. &QL; 
Manning camp
</P>
<P>
   Forward &UR; Danny Manning announced his annual summer basketball
camps for children grades 3-12 will be held July 19-23 at Horizon
High School. The focus of the camp is fundamentals, sportsmanship
and fun. Cost is $100. For more information, call (602) 996-2473 or
(602) 996-5009. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
