<SLUG> BC-XIRCOM-SHARES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
XIRCOM SHARES REBOUND FROM FALL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY BEN SULLIVAN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES -- Shares in Xircom Inc. rose more than 14 percent
Monday after the Thousand Oaks-based company announced a new line
of modems and investment bank CIBC Oppenheimer initiated coverage
of the company's stock with a ``strong buy'' rating.
</P>
<P>
   The stock rose by $3.1875, or 14.17 percent, to $25.6875. More
than 1 million shares were traded, roughly 50 percent more than the
issue's 30-day average volume.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to the positive rating, analyst Martin Pyykkonen at
CIBC Oppenheimer projected a $40 per share 12-month target price
for Xircom stock. While the New York-based investment bank has
tracked Xircom for several years, it had dropped official coverage
when a previous analyst left the firm.
</P>
<P>
   The vote of confidence was welcome news to the Thousand Oaks
company. Xircom stock had been on the decline for two months,
falling from a peak of about $46 in early February to as low as
$18.8125 on April 7. While the company's financial performance has
been strong so far in 1999, its shares have suffered collateral
damage from two separate quarters.
</P>
<P>
   The first concern came in February when 3Com Corp., maker of the
popular Palm Pilot digital assistant and a Xircom competitor in the
modem arena, warned that its own earnings were suffering from
declining margins and disappointing sales. 3Com hinted its problems
were being felt across the industry, causing concern among
investors that Xircom also would be hit.
</P>
<P>
   That proved not to be the case. Xircom announced second-quarter
earnings of $10.8 million, a 227 percent gain over the previous
year and a $1 million boost over the first quarter that ended Dec.
31.
</P>
<P>
   ``3Com's financial performance has not been good, and the most
comparable industry constituent ... is 3Com,'' said analyst Phil
Leigh at investment bank Raymond James. ``But that's an invalid
assumption.''
</P>
<P>
   The other trouble for Xircom came when No. 1 computer maker
Compaq Computers missed analysts' earnings expectations, leading to
the ouster of the company's chief executive and chief financial
officer. That sent shivers throughout the computer sector,
touching, among others, Xircom.
</P>
<P>
   ``My basic stance is not that there's some new information out
there on Xircom, but that two extraneous events that don't relate
to the company affected its price,'' Pyykkonen said.
</P>
<P>
   Xircom announced before the market opened Monday that it has
entered the hand-held personal-computer market with a new line of
modems for computers operating on the Windows CE platform. The PC
cards provide modem, Ethernet and wireless connections to data
networks. Analysts said sales of the devices will have little
impact initially on Xircom earnings, but as sales of personal
digital assistants increase, so too should sales of the
peripherals.
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
