<P>
   RANDY-NEWMAN _ For nearly 30 years, singer/songwriter Randy
Newman has been making critically acclaimed music, from the
bittersweet ``Rednecks'' album in the '70s to his '80s pop hit
``Short People'' to Grammy and Oscar nominations in the '98 for his
film scores. Newman is back at the keyboards with a new solo CD
coming out in June, and unveils the fresh tunes at an intimate show
tonight (May 5) at Variety Playhouse. We talk with Newman and
others. (Mlongino, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   SHAVER _ WACO, Texas _ Billy Joe Shaver has a ready quip for
those wondering about the title of his new album Electric Shaver.
``When my boy was born in Waco, I tried to name him that, but
wouldn't nobody go for it,'' he jokes. The joke within his joke is
that between Shaver and his son Eddie, Electric Shaver really could
be named after Eddie, whose blistering guitar work powers the
album, energizing the rough-hewn beauty in the senior Shaver's
lyrics. (Hoover, Waco Herald-Tribune) MOVED.
</P>
