<P>
   PRAYER-DAY-PROFILE _ AUSTIN _ A mini-profile of Evelyn W.
Davison, Central Texas coordinator for the National Day of Prayer,
which is Thursday. For several years Davidson has been the prayer
parent for George W. Bush, praying for him daily and keeping in
regular communication through writing and his aids. Its her job to
let Bush know when he steps out of line with the Bible. Evelyn says
her only criticism so far is that his jogging shorts are really
ugly so she bought him a new pair. Davidson started off a marathon
Bible reading at 10 p.m. Sunday; it will continue until the prayer
breakfast Thursday morning. (Perkes, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
