<SLUG> BC-STAR-WARS-LIST-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HOTLIST EXTRA: STAR WARS 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  (Eds.: Also see: Star-Wars-Web) 
 
By DWIGHT SILVERMAN 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON _ A look at 10 of the top Web sites dedicated to ``Star
Wars.''
</P>
<P>
   1. Star Wars _ www.starwars.com
</P>
<P>
   Here's the source of the Force, the official ``Star Wars'' Web
site from Lucasfilm. You can download the trailer for ``Episode
I,'' learn about characters in the film and, of course, give George
Lucas money online in exchange for Star Wars baubles and trinkets.
</P>
<P>
   2. Star Wars Database _ www.swdatabase.com
</P>
<P>
   If it has to do with any aspect of the ``Star Wars'' universe,
you'll find it in this exhaustive, searchable listing. The site is
bristling with message boards, chat rooms, rumors and daily news
summaries as ``Episode I's'' release gets closer.
</P>
<P>
   3. The Completely Unofficial Star Wars Encyclopedia _
www.mindspring.com/bobvitas/swenc.htm &UR;
</P>
<P>
   &LR; ``Star Trek'' fans have nothing on the obsessives that focus on
``Star Wars,'' as witnessed by this incredible, work-in-progress
online encyclopedia. It lovingly documents every tiny factoid in
the ``Star Wars'' universe, cataloging them alphabetically.
</P>
<P>
   4. NewsDroid _ www.newsdroid.com
</P>
<P>
   Need detailed news about the ``Star Wars'' movie, and you need
it now? NewsDroid, billed as ``Headline News for Star Wars fans,''
offer news tidbits in everything from the films to comic books to
collectibles and games.
</P>
<P>
   5. Force.net _ www.theforce.net
</P>
<P>
   This Houston-based site is generally considered one of the best
fan and news sites for ``Star Wars'' junkies. It's a full-blown
fanzine, complete with news, discussion forums, trivia, collectors'
information, feature stories and even a humor area.
</P>
<P>
   6. Star Wars Search Engine _ www.starwarsnet.com
</P>
<P>
   Looking for specific ``Star Wars'' information? You know it's on
the Net somewhere, but you just can't find it? This search engine
checks the dozens _ maybe hundreds _ of Star Wars fan sites to
bring you what you need.
</P>
<P>
   7. Echo Station _ www.echostation.com
</P>
<P>
   Here's a site for the serious ``Star Wars'' fan. Get free
Web-based e-mail with one of two ``Star Wars''-related domain names
(coruscant.net or bothanspy.com) via this site. While you're
waiting for mail to arrive, play Squadron XWord, a crossword game.
</P>
<P>
   8. Greater Gulf Coast Star Wars Collectors _ www.swgeeks.com
</P>
<P>
   Those Han Solo and Princess Leia action figures you sold at a
garage sale in 1982? They're now worth big bucks. Learn more about
the Force's effects on the collectibles market.
</P>
<P>
   9. JediKnight.Net _ www.jediknight.net
</P>
<P>
   LucasArts, the game-development arm of the George Lucas empire,
has churned out a slew of ``Star Wars''-related computer games.
This site tracks them, providing news of new titles and software
patches and updates for existing ones.
</P>
<P>
   10. Hardware Wars _ www.mwp.com/mwp/Hardwars.html
</P>
<P>
   Tired of the hype? Get some vengeful satisfaction by ordering
the classic movie parody ``Hardware Wars,'' which came out just
months after the original ``Star Wars'' film. Thrill to Princess
Anne-Droid's cinnamon-bun hairstyle, or watch steam irons battle
waffle irons in hyperspace.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
