<SLUG> BC-WINE-TASTINGS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WINE TASTINGS: AGE IS A VIRTUE 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Pelligrini Cabernet Sauvignon Cloverdale Ranch 1996, Alexander
Valley, Calif. About $17.
</P>
<P>
   Some vines at the Pelligrini Cloverdale Ranch in Sonoma County,
Calif., are more than 40 years old, which prompted the winemaker,
Merry Edwards, to do two fermentations.
</P>
<P>
   She put the old vine grapes, about 40 percent of the total, into
small open-top tanks and the rest in stainless-steel rotary
fermenters. The wine was then aged for 15 months in American and
French oak barrels.
</P>
<P>
   The result is a rich, plummy, opaque wine with a nice, long
finish. It is an elegant wine and a very good value.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
