Albania Tuesday with fresh reports of Serb forces using brutality
and wanton killing to push ethnic Albanians from Kosovo. More than
6,000 refugees had crossed the border from different parts of the
embattled Yugoslav province by early evening, many repeating
similar stories of forces demanding money from ethnic Albanian
refugees, and gunning down those who didn't comply. They came in on
buses after walking for for days, and trucks. A long caravan of
tractors came across after winding over a hazardous mountain road.
Developing. (Kunstel). (Kunstel, Cox News Service). 20. WITH
PHOTOS.
