   E N T E R T A I N M E N T &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SWINDELL-BOOKSHELF &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The recent PBS re-airing of the late Laurie Lee's
``Cider With Rosie'' on ``Masterpiece Theatre'' has given me a
thirst for reading more of this once-to-a-world writer's work. Most
of all, I wish to read ``Cider With Rosie.'' By LARRY SWINDELL.
Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-MITCHELL &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DALLAS _ Film critic Elvis Mitchell says, yes, Dallas' USA Film
Festival made some odd choices _ but isn't that what film festivals
are all about? Besides, some of the choices _ such as screening
``Animal House'' _ worked. By ELVIS MITCHELL. Story has moved in
``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
