<SLUG> BC-COX-CHECKS-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Cox to offer bill-paying via CheckFree
 &HT;    By Charles Haddad
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ In a first for the cable TV industry, Cox
Communications will use the electronic banking services of
Atlanta-based CheckFree to allow its customers to receive monthly
statements and pay their bills via computer.
</P>
<P>
   The service will be available to all of Cox Communications' 3.8
million subscribers nationwide as of Sept. 1.
</P>
<P>
   The service would work in two ways. Customers could pay their
bills through a CheckFree Web site called E-Bill and located at
www.mybills.com/ebill. Or they could pay bills through electronic
banking software such as Quicken or Microsoft Money.
</P>
<P>
   The deal also represents the first time the company's customers
can receive and pay for a variety of new services in one statement.
The electronic statement would include fees for both cable TV and
telephone service _ but not yet for high-speed access to the
Internet. Cox now offers in nationwide markets these services:
cable TV, local and long-distance telephone service and high-speed
access to the Internet through cable modems.
</P>
<P>
   ``With this agreement, Cox Communications demonstrates
innovation in meeting customer needs and delivering leading
technology among providers of communications services,'' said Scott
Hatfield, Cox Communications' chief information officer.
</P>
<P>
   Cox represents the 49th big corporate customer that has signed
up to use CheckFree's system. CheckFree has 2.8 million customers
using its electronic banking services. Its software is the backbone
of the electronic banking systems of SunTrust and First Union, for
example.
</P>
<P>
   Cox Communications is controlled by Atlanta-based media
conglomerate Cox Enterprises Inc.
</P>
<P>
   Charles Haddad writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
