<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Wednesday, May 5, and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   SILICON-BANK (Westlake Village, Calif.) _ Silicon Valley Bank,
one of the leading financiers behind the Bay Area high-tech hotbed,
is opening a branch in Westlake Village because ``the region has
become quite attractive to start-ups and venture capital investment
in the region has tripled over the past three years,'' the company
said Tuesday. By Ben Sullivan.
</P>
<P>
   AMWEST-RESTRUCTURE (Calabasas, Calif.) _ Amwest Insurance Co. is
withdrawing from the Arizona car market and California homeowners
market, the Calabasas-based company announced Tuesday, in its
continuing attempt at restructuring its business. By Deborah
Adamson.
</P>
<P>
   FHS-EARNINGS (Los Angeles) _ Foundation Health Systems Inc. is
expected to report improved earnings Wednesday on growth at its
HealthNet HMO. Still, the company's stock is wallowing, after a
year of poor results. By Ben Sullivan.
</P>
