 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; MEDIATOR &LR;  _ (Sinton) Each year litigants in the United State spend
billions of dollars duking it out in court. But with rising costs
and clogged courts, individuals, businesses and governments
increasingly are taking a more civil approach to settling their
differences.
</P>
<P>
   They are turning to alternative dispute resolution, or ADR, and
hiring former judges, attorneys and business veterans to mediate
and arbitrate their grievances. One of the most successful of these
so-called ``neutrals'' is former San Francisco Judge Daniel
Weinstein, who last Thursday won the San Francisco Trial Lawyer
Association's first annual Distinguished Mediator Award.
