<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Washington) _ Russian envoy Viktor Chernomyrdin
meets with Vice President Al Gore and other U.S. officials to hear
President Clinton's offer to suspend the NATO bombing of Yugoslavia
and negotiate a peace force for Kosovo. The Senate, meanwhile,
shelves an attempt to give Clinton the authority to use ``all
necessary force'' against Yugoslavia. By GREG McDONALD and NANCY
MATHIS.
</P>
