   HOLLYWOOD-VIOLENCE (Washington) _ Top senators warn the makers
of violent films and video games to stop targeting children in
their advertising or the government would do it for them. ``None of
us wants to resort to regulation, but if the entertainment industry
does not do something to change their methods, we will be forced to
act,'' says Sen. Joseph Lieberman, D-Conn. By MARK HELM. (Already
filed.)
