<P>
   GOLD-BATTLE (Washington) _ Deep within a mountain in northern
Washington are microscopic veins of gold worth tens of millions of
dollars. A Texas mining company, Battle Mountain Gold, is so
convinced of the value of that gold that it spent $80 million over
the past seven years winning a variety of permits and legal battles
to extract the ore. But a month ago, the Clinton administration
announced that, under a little-known provision of an 1872 mining
law, the project could not proceed as planned. Now a largely local
dispute has turned into a congressional battle with national
implications.
