featured dancers in ``Fosse.'' ``In ballet, you have to keep a
higher level technically, so in one way it's physically more
demanding,'' says Ms. Parkinson, who at 25 is the youngest dancer
in the show. (Sara Krulwich/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT22) NAPA VALLEY, Calif. -- May 4, 1999 -- WINE-TALK, 5-04 --
Phylloxera, the dreaded parasite that had devastated the vines of
Europe and California a century before, sparked an epidemic in the
Napa Valley in the early '90s. But by 1996, tighter plantings and
new kinds of trellises yielded more flavorful grapes at this Robert
Mondavi vineyard. (New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT21) HANOK, South Korea -- May 4, 1999 --
KOREA-GENERATION-GAP, 5-04 -- ``When I was young I did what my
mother-in-law said,'' said Park Ki Soon, 70, as she used a wooden
paddle to churn a couldron of beans. ``But now my daughter-in-law
doesn't listen to me.'' Korea was one of the last places to open up
to Western influences, for until a century ago it was an ancient
kingdom that operated on Confucian traditions and deeply regimented
customs. Those customs, especially respect for the elderly,
permeated Korean society until the last few decades. (Nicholas
Kristof/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT20) NEW YORK -- May 4, 1999 -- LOUIMA-TRIAL, 5-04 --
Attorney Marvin Kornberg, right, escorts New York City Police
