<HEADLINE>
INJURED ROENICK RETURNS TO COYOTES LINEUP 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB MCMANAMAN  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - Coyotes center Jeremy Roenick, expected to be
sidelined for team's entire playoff season because of a shattered
jaw and fractured right thumb, was given medical clearance to play
in Game 7 Tuesday night of the Coyotes' first-round series against
the St. Louis Blues.
</P>
<P>
   The Coyotes' leading scorer had hinted for the past several days
he would try to return to the lineup, but it was considered a
longshot and thought it wouldn't be until late in the second round,
at that, if Phoenix were to advance.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm going to have to talk to a bunch of people to see if
they'll let me play,'' Roenick said Tuesday morning by telephone.
``My day's going to be full of negotiations, that's for sure. It's
a delicate issue, I know, but hey, we've got to win.''
</P>
<P>
   General Manager Bobby Smith announced about an hour before game
time that the team's medical staff had given Roenick clearance to
play.
</P>
<P>
   Roenick, 29, had his jaw shattered in three places on April 14
in Dallas on a hit from Stars captain Derian Hatcher, who was
suspended seven games for the incident. Roenick's thumb also was
broken on the same play due to a slash from Craig Ludwig.
</P>
<P>
   Hatcher missed the Stars' final two regular-season games and all
four games of Dallas' first-round series sweep of the Mighty Ducks
of Anaheim. He also must sit out the Stars' first game of Round 2
against the winner of the Coyotes-Blues series.
</P>
<P>
   Roenick had a specially-designed, protective faceguard attached
to his helmet, which apparently met approval from the NHL. The
10-year veteran, who led the Coyotes with 72 points (24 goals, 48
assists) in 78 games, had two steel plates inserted to realign his
jaw in a 5{-hour operation the day after the injury.
</P>
<P>
   At that time, the Coyotes announced he was done for the season,
regardless of how far the club advanced in the playoffs.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
